{"type":"message","id":"bc67a300","parentId":"5fab0307","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:19:39.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ken4suoo5kt1_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5934\n[master 1634088] pulse: 2026-03-24 161916\n 3 files changed, 217 insertions(+), 128 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 161916.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 161916 - The Phase 1 \"next\" task is Conditional Content Analysis - the empirical test that distinguishes CFI (Pattern Information, compression Layer 1) from true causal tokens. This is the critical experiment to complete the CFI compression work.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"brisk-bloom","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5934\n[master 1634088] pulse: 2026-03-24 161916\n 3 files changed, 217 insertions(+), 128 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 161916.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 161916 - The Phase 1 \"next\" task is Conditional Content Analysis - the empirical test that distinguishes CFI (Pattern Information, compression Layer 1) from true causal tokens. This is the critical experiment to complete the CFI compression work.\n","name":"powershell Bypass"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774383579053}}
{"type":"message","id":"6731551d","parentId":"bc67a300","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:19:39.062Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ken4suoo5kt1_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 161814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\n**Current State:**\r\n- Phase 1 is in progress: \"Compression primitives - CFI analysis complete, next is conditional content analysis\"\r\n- The immediate next experiment is \"Conditional Content Analysis\" which is the highest priority\r\n- This experiment tests whether moderate-frequency tokens (freq=60-80%) actually cause changes in the next pulse's research content\r\n\r\n**The Experiment:**\r\n- Take tokens like \"compression\" (freq=199, CFI=0.995), \"causal\" (freq=162, CFI=0.981), \"phase\" (freq=187, CFI=0.946)\r\n- For moderate-frequency tokens, split pulse pairs into T-present and T-absent groups\r\n- Compare: does research content of next-pulse differ between groups?\r\n- If no difference: CFI measures scaffolding\r\n- If yes: tokens are genuinely causal\r\n\r\n**What I need to do:**\r\nThe next concrete action is to implement this conditional content analysis. This would involve:\r\n1. Writing a script or analysis to examine the pulses and compare content when a token is present vs absent\r\n2. Running the analysis on the available pulse data\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available:\r\n- Pulse directory: `pulses/` containing pulse files\r\n- I need to examine pulses and compare content based on token presence\r\n\r\nI'll create a new analysis document that describes the experiment design and then implement it by analyzing the existing pulse data.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully - I should implement the actual analysis. Let me create a script that:\r\n1. Loads pulse data\r\n2. For a token like \"causal\" (freq=162), finds pairs where the token appears in pulse N\r\n3. Compares pulse N+1 content when token is present vs absent\r\n4. Measures whether there's a difference\r\n\r\nThis is the highest priority next step according to the goals. Let me implement this.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll examine the pulse directory to understand the structure and content, identifying how to systematically analyze token patterns across the pulse collection. I'll design a Python script that can parse the pulse files, extract relevant metadata, and perform comparative content analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1 is blocked on the Conditional Content Analysis experiment—the highest priority next step that distinguishes Pattern Information from Causal Information empirically. The pulses directory contains the data needed to run this analysis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement the Conditional Content Analysis by creating a Python script that compares pulse content when candidate tokens are present vs absent, then run it on the available pulse data to determine if moderate-frequency tokens are genuinely causal or just scaffolding.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nConditional Content Analysis - Phase 1.1\r\nTests whether moderate-frequency tokens are causally connected to next-pulse content.\r\n\r\nHypothesis:\r\n- If next-pulse content differs significantly between T-present and T-absent groups: T is genuinely causal\r\n- If no difference: CFI measures scaffolding (Pattern Information only)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom difflib import SequenceMatcher\r\n\r\nPULSES_DIR = Path(\"pulses\")\r\nCANDIDATE_TOKENS = [\"causal\", \"compression\", \"phase\", \"token\", \"pulse\", \"research\"]\r\n\r\ndef extract_text_content(pulse_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract research content from pulse (excluding metadata).\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    # Remove frontmatter-like patterns\r\n    content = re.sub(r'^#.*?\\n---.*?\\n', '', content, flags=re.DOTALL)\r\n    content = re.sub(r'\\n---\\n.*', '', content, flags=re.DOTALL)\r\n    return content.strip()\r\n\r\ndef get_token_presence(pulses, token):\r\n    \"\"\"Split pulses into T-present and T-absent groups.\"\"\"\r\n    present = []\r\n    absent = []\r\n    token_lower = token.lower()\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(pulses)):\r\n        curr_content = extract_text_content(pulses[i])\r\n        token_found = token_lower in curr_content.lower()\r\n        \r\n        if token_found:\r\n            present.append(i)\r\n        else:\r\n            absent.append(i)\r\n    \r\n    return present, absent\r\n\r\ndef content_similarity(text1, text2):\r\n    \"\"\"Return similarity ratio between two texts.\"\"\"\r\n    return SequenceMatcher(None, text1, text2).ratio()\r\n\r\ndef analyze_next_pulse_content(pulses, token, group):\r\n    \"\"\"For each index in group, get the content of the next pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    next_contents = []\r\n    \r\n    for idx in group:\r\n        if idx + 1 < len(pulses):\r\n            next_contents.append(extract_text_content(pulses[idx + 1]))\r\n    \r\n    return next_contents\r\n\r\ndef compute_group_metrics(pulses, token):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute metrics comparing T-present vs T-absent next-pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    present_idx, absent_idx = get_token_presence(pulses, token)\r\n    \r\n    if len(present_idx) < 5 or len(absent_idx) < 5:\r\n        return None, {\"error\": \"Insufficient data\", \"present\": len(present_idx), \"absent\": len(absent_idx)}\r\n    \r\n    present_next = analyze_next_pulse_content(pulses, token, present_idx)\r\n    absent_next = analyze_next_pulse_content(pulses, token, absent_idx)\r\n    \r\n    if not present_next or not absent_next:\r\n        return None, {\"error\": \"No next-pulse data\"}\r\n    \r\n    # Compute internal consistency: avg similarity within group\r\n    def avg_internal_similarity(contents):\r\n        if len(contents) < 2:\r\n            return 1.0\r\n        total = 0\r\n        count = 0\r\n        for i in range(len(contents)):\r\n            for\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 16:18:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774383579058}}
